            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "At least in PyCharm, you can create a run configuration for the Flask command, as you would for a normal Python script. Presumably you can do that in any other debugger. Then you set breakpoints like normal.\r\n\r\nClick also has facilities for calling commands programmatically, if you do want to write a separate script. http://click.pocoo.org/dev/testing/"
